Method Detail

createUI

void createUI(YouScopeFrame frame)
Is called when the post-processor should start to do whatever it is made to do. The post-processor should either provide some possibilities for the user to interact with it (e.g. to configure or stop the post-processor doing whatever it does), which should be initialized in the frame, or a message or something similar that the processor is started, which should then be initialized in the frame. However, the frame should not be made visible.

Parameters:
frame - The frame in which the graphical elements of the post-processor should be initialized.
